      • setCallback

        public void setCallback(RouteCallback<Route> callback)
        Optionally, You can have a callback attached to a predefined route, which allows you to put code inside to be ran when the route URL is called. This is helpful in cases, like a logout URL where when called, you'd probably want to run a code block to log the user out.
        Parameters:
        callback - The callback function to trigger when the predefined route is called.

      • setTargetClass

        public void setTargetClass(java.lang.Class<? extends Activity> targetClass)
        Optionally, you can specify an Android activity to open when a predefined route is called. For instance, if you had a URL like "/users/:userId/projects/:projectId", you'd probably want to open the project activity. Within this activity you can access the Bundle within the Route object and determine behaviour accordingly.
        Parameters:
        targetClass - The Android Activity to open when the predefined route is called.
